.TH "funzy_wav2k7" "1" "2026-06-09" "" "funzyto770 User Manuals"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
funzy_wav2k7 - convert a cassette WAV audio recording to Thomson TO7 .k7
format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]funzy_wav2k7\f[R] \f[I]file.wav\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]funzy_wav2k7\f[R] converts a WAV audio file recorded from a Thomson
TO7 or TO7-70 cassette tape into the .k7 binary format used by the
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R] emulator and the companion utilities
\f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R](1) and \f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R](1).
.PP
The input WAV file must be 8-bit mono recorded at 44100 Hz.
The output file takes the name of the input file with the \f[B].wav\f[R]
extension replaced by \f[B].k7\f[R].
.PP
If the conversion does not yield a usable .k7 file, check that the
recording level was adequate.
If necessary, apply equalisation by boosting the 4.5 kHz\[en]6.3 kHz
frequency band.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
This program accepts no options.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]file.wav\f[R]
Input audio file (8-bit mono, 44100 Hz).
.TP
\f[I]file.k7\f[R]
Output cassette tape image in TO7 format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Convert a WAV recording to .k7 format:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzy_wav2k7 myprog.wav
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
This produces \f[B]myprog.k7\f[R], which can then be loaded by the
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R] emulator.
.PP
Convert a ROM dump for extraction with \f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R](1):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzy_wav2k7 romto770.wav
funzy_getrom romto770.k7
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R](1), \f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R](1)
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
